subSubSection.paragraph:
(
Figures 87–89
)

Erect, short to medium-length, whitish pilosity moderately abundant on head, no hairs> 0.7–0.8× MOD. Moderately abundant suberect to semidecumbent pilosity on scape; abundant decumbent hairs on funicular segments. Legs with moderately abundant suberect to decumbent whitish setae. Rest of body with erect, moderately dense, medium-length, whitish setae, longest about 0.8–1.0× MOD. Body concolorous medium to dark brownish-orange or with petiolar node, postpetiole, gaster, and legs slightly darker than rest of body (
Figure 87
).
